### Database Performance Indexes (`5d807d7ec`)

**Problem**: 35 hot columns (status, created_at, recorded_at, moderation_status, submission_time, creation_time) across 10 coordinator-api domain model files were frequently filtered/ordered in SQL queries but lacked indexes. Additionally, 11 composite indexes on the agent_identity tables (cross_chain_mappings, identity_verifications, agent_wallets) were commented out and never enabled.

**Fix**: Added `index=True` to all 35 single-column indexes, chosen by cross-referencing actual SQL query patterns (`.where()`/`.order_by()`) in the storage/router/service layers. Enabled all 11 composite indexes. Added a new `expires_at` index for the identity verification expiry sweep query.

**Alembic migration**: `apps/coordinator-api/alembic/versions/add_query_performance_indexes.py` ‚Äî uses `if_not_exists=True` for idempotency, since `SQLModel.metadata.create_all` only adds indexes to fresh DBs.

**Verification**: All 46 expected indexes confirmed present via `SQLModel.metadata.create_all` on in-memory SQLite (174 total indexes in schema).

**Files changed** (10 domain + 1 migration):
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/domain/agent.py` ‚Äî `AgentExecution.status`, `AgentStepExecution.status`
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/domain/bounty.py` ‚Äî `Bounty.status`/`creation_time`, `BountySubmission.status`/`submission_time`, `AgentStake.status`
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/domain/trading.py` ‚Äî `TradeRequest`/`TradeMatch`/`TradeNegotiation` status + created_at
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/domain/analytics.py` ‚Äî `MarketMetric.recorded_at`, status+created_at on `MarketInsight`/`AnalyticsAlert`/`AnalyticsReport`/`DashboardConfig`/`DataCollectionJob`/`AlertRule`
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/domain/certification.py` ‚Äî status on `AgentCertification`/`VerificationRecord`/`PartnershipProgram`/`AgentPartnership` + `PartnershipProgram.created_at`
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/domain/rewards.py` ‚Äî `RewardDistribution`/`RewardMilestone` status + created_at
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/domain/reputation.py` ‚Äî `CommunityFeedback.moderation_status`/`created_at`
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/domain/community.py` ‚Äî `AgentSolution.status`, `CommunityPost.created_at`
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/domain/developer_platform.py` ‚Äî `BountyTask.created_at`
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/contexts/agent_identity/domain/agent_identity.py` ‚Äî `AgentIdentity.status`, enabled 11 composite indexes, new `expires_at` index
- `apps/coordinator-api/alembic/versions/add_query_performance_indexes.py` ‚Äî new migration

### CLI Duplicate Removal (`00ab4ab25`)

**Problem**: `cli/utils/dual_mode_wallet_adapter.py` (626 lines) was a stale pre-package-layout copy of `cli/aitbc_cli/utils/dual_mode_wallet_adapter.py`. All importers used the `aitbc_cli.utils` version; nobody imported the `cli.utils` version.

**Fix**: Deleted the stale copy. Also fixed a missing trailing newline in `cli/aitbc_cli/commands/explorer.py` flagged by ruff.

### Blockchain Explorer Decomposition (`60c2522c2`)

**Problem**: `apps/blockchain-explorer/main.py` was 1,442 lines with all 19 API routes defined inline.

**Fix**: Split into 11 files:
- `validation.py` (29 lines) ‚Äî SSRF validation patterns (`TX_HASH_PATTERN`, `CHAIN_ID_PATTERN`)
- `models.py` (29 lines) ‚Äî Pydantic request models (`TransactionSearch`, `BlockSearch`, `AnalyticsRequest`)
- `chain_client.py` (338 lines) ‚Äî RPC/DB helpers, config constants, `normalize_block()`, `get_chain_head()`, `get_transaction()`, `get_block()`, `get_latest_blocks()`
- `routers/chains.py` (32 lines) ‚Äî 2 routes
- `routers/blocks.py` (352 lines) ‚Äî 5 routes
- `routers/transactions.py` (176 lines) ‚Äî 3 routes
- `routers/analytics.py` (317 lines) ‚Äî 5 routes
- `routers/search.py` (126 lines) ‚Äî 2 routes
- `routers/export.py` (120 lines) ‚Äî 2 routes
- `main.py` (54 lines) ‚Äî app factory with `include_router` calls, `/health` route, uvicorn entrypoint

All 19 API routes preserved with identical paths, signatures, and response formats. Uses absolute imports since the hyphenated directory name prevents standard package imports.

### Exchange Decomposition + Dead Code Removal (`2f629910f`)

**Problem**: `apps/exchange/simple_exchange_api.py` was 1,209 lines (stdlib `http.server`) with all handlers inline. Additionally, `apps/exchange/api/` (4 files, 422 lines) was a dead previous decomposition attempt ‚Äî zero importers anywhere in the codebase.

**Fix**: Split `simple_exchange_api.py` into 3 files:
- `db.py` (125 lines) ‚Äî `get_db_path()`, `init_db()`, `create_mock_trades()`
- `handlers.py` (1,040 lines) ‚Äî `BaseHandler` (shared `send_json_response`/`do_OPTIONS`/`_read_json_body`), `ExchangeAPIHandler`, `WalletAPIHandler`
- `simple_exchange_api.py` (38 lines) ‚Äî `run_server()` + argparse entrypoint

Deleted the dead `apps/exchange/api/` package (`__init__.py`, `database.py`, `handlers.py`, `server.py`). The `api/database.py` content survived as `apps/exchange/db.py` (renamed by git). Tests use `exchange_api.py` (FastAPI version), unaffected.

### DatabaseConfig Consolidation (`7ce7484e6`)

**Problem**: `DatabaseConfig` with `effective_url` was copy-pasted in 4 locations: `packages/aitbc-shared/aitbc_shared/core/config.py` (canonical), `apps/agent-management/src/app/core/config.py`, `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/config.py`, `apps/edge/src/aitbc_edge/config.py`. Each service reimplemented the adapter URL formatter with per-service DB filenames, causing drift.

**Fix**: Added a `db_filename: str = "service.db"` class attribute to the shared `DatabaseConfig`. The shared `effective_url` now uses it for both SQLite (`f"sqlite:///{DATA_DIR}/data/{db_filename}"`) and PostgreSQL (`f"{adapter}://localhost:5432/{db_filename.removesuffix('.db')}"`). Services set only `db_filename` instead of reimplementing `effective_url`.

**Per-service changes**:
- **agent-management**: `db_filename = "agent_management.db"`; dropped 12-line `effective_url` override, redundant `model_config`, `DATA_DIR` import
- **coordinator-api**: `db_filename = "coordinator.db"`; dropped 12-line `effective_url` override; extracted 4 repeated `os.getenv("ENVIRONMENT", ...)` calls into `_is_production()` helper; simplified `get_effective_database_url()` to delegate to `database.effective_url`
- **edge**: Replaced hardcoded `postgresql+asyncpg://...:password@localhost:5432/aitbc_edge` with shared adapter pattern (`db_filename="aitbc_edge.db"`, SQLite by default, postgres via env var); replaced placeholder JWT secret `"your-secret-key-change-in-production"` with empty string (must be set via env); fixed `main.py` to use `app_host`/`app_port` from shared `ServiceSettings` instead of non-existent `api_host`/`api_port`
- **shared-core**: Converted to thin re-export shim from `aitbc_shared`

### JWT Auth Repoint + Dead Config Removal (`96de61900`)

**Problem**: `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/auth/jwt_auth.py` imported settings from `config_pg.py` (a legacy PostgreSQL-only config), not the unified `config.py`. `config_pg.py` and `storage/db_pg.py` (343 lines combined) were dead code with only each other as importers.

**Fix**:
- Repointed `jwt_auth.py` import from `..config_pg` to `..config` ‚Äî JWT fields (`jwt_secret`, `jwt_algorithm`, `jwt_expiration_hours`) are inherited from `BaseAITBCConfig`
- Added `jwt_secret: str = ""` override in unified `Settings` (base defaults to `None` which would break `jwt.encode()`)
- Fixed `database_async.py` `init_async_db()` to use `settings.effective_database_url` (respects test mode) instead of `settings.database.effective_url` (bypassed test mode)
- Deleted `config_pg.py` (98 lines) and `db_pg.py` (245 lines) ‚Äî zero remaining importers

### Final Config Cleanup (`0ab95b4a3`)

**Problem**: `Settings.effective_database_url` property and `test_database_url` field in `config.py` were dead code after the previous repoint ‚Äî all call sites now use `settings.database.effective_url` directly.

**Fix**:
- Replaced `settings.effective_database_url` with `str(settings.database.effective_url)` in `database_async.py` (lines 44 and 90)
- Removed `effective_database_url` property from `config.py`
- Removed `test_database_url` field and its env var override
- The test conftest creates its own engine directly (`create_engine("sqlite:///:memory:")`) and never read `settings.effective_database_url`

### Systemd Symlink Audit

Verified all 12 `aitbc*.service` symlinks in `/etc/systemd/system/` resolve to non-empty service files. Zero dangling symlinks. (The `aitbc-recovery` symlink was fixed in the original v0.5.11 release.)

